According to a report on December 5, Apple is working with Baidu to launch Apple Intelligence features in China, but the two sides have encountered some obstacles in their cooperation: 
Baidu has always had difficulties in understanding prompts from large AI models and responding correctly to common scenarios raised by iPhone users; 
Apple's privacy policy also does not allow the collection of user data using AI queries, but Baidu hopes to save and analyze this data.
